Raised opercular margin well developed and smooth. Operculum with 12 pairs of paleae, long, golden brown, subacute, curved dorsally, with compact tips. First pair of tentacular cirri arising from anterior edge of segment 2. Ventral ridge connecting second pair of tentacular cirri on segment 3 incised, forming glandular lobes. Chaetiger 2 with anteroventral lobe large and broad; anterior margin of lobe crenulate, posterodorsal lobe absent (
Fig. 14A
).

Posterior scaphe and abdomen distinctly separated. Posterior 5 segments fused to form a flattened plate or scaphe broader than long, with crenulated margins. Scaphe with an anal flap and dorsal papilla. Eight pairs of scaphal hooks, broad, blunt, brown (
Fig. 12D
). Prominent glandular areas present on chaetigers 4 to 17, and ventral areas of segments 1 to 6 also glandular. Triangular gland present between segments 2 and 3, situated mid-ventrally. Segments 3 and 4 with raised glandular anterior margins extending across venter. Paired nephridial papillae on chaetiger 1, inserted ventrally at the base of the second pair of branchiae.
